The paper focuses on audio representation and event detection in videos, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. 

- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is the most likely category, as it specifically deals with audio processing and analysis. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possibility, as the paper uses a dataset of consumer-produced videos and discusses how different models leverage the intrinsic structure of the data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possibility, as the paper proposes a novel two-phase method for audio representation that involves optimizing on Grassmannian manifolds. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility, as the paper deals with event detection in videos and uses a video corpus dataset. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possibility, as event detection in videos often involves analyzing both audio and visual information.
